translated: Holmqvist, Carl Erik Gunnar, provincial doctor, Lessebo, born on March 31, 1898 in Lund to Jonas H. and Carolina Tullberg. Married to Greta Gunhild Gabriella Lindell in 1925. Children: Birgitta Margaretha Carolina, born in 1926, Ann-Mari, born in 1930. He passed his studentexamen (university entrance exam) in 1916 and earned his medical degree in 1920 and licentiate of medicine in 1925, both from Lund University. He worked as an assistant doctor at Eksjö Hospital in 1924-26, and as an understudy doctor at Apelvikens Coastal Sanatorium in 1926-28, and at Mora Hospital in 1928-31, where he was acting chief doctor for three months. He was appointed as a doctor at Lund University Hospital's medical department and also as an understudy doctor at Högbo Sanatorium in 1931, and acted as a temporary provincial doctor in Malungs, Löberöds, Fjugesta and Nås districts in 1931-32. He became the provincial doctor in Stegeborgs district from 1932-38, and then in Lessebo district from 1938 onwards. He went on a study trip in 1937. He was an amateur violinist who studied at a music conservatory and performed as a soloist throughout the country and on the radio several times with his own program.
